originalText.text: To be honest I'm I'm regular coming here because is near by my apartment. Have no choice but to bring my stuff to wash here .Here is the thing this place need some fix up on the machine some of the washer machine doesn't wash very efficiently. Beware parents with kids running around .I remember a couple weeks ago my clothes was in the washer machine and some random kid try to open my machine while it was washing smh.They should put a label for customers to watch over there kids this is not a playground.

originalText.text: I'm a regular here as it is around the block from my shelter I have had two times where the dryer didn't work properly with the smaller dryer and it's the same dryer I always use if it's available but I explained that it says error and stop spinning in the middle of my drying cycle and had to press start again and when I left and came back it stopped again but ran my time out and when I told the lady what happened she tries to make it seem as though it stopped cause I had my thin sheets in there with my clothes when it ran out of time it still kept spinning on its own and I told the lady and she said it's normal that it does that when I feel it's not normal .. and today I was grabbing my clothes out the dryer  dryer number 23 and it spinned on its own while taking my clothes out the dryer and I put it on 25 minutes only to waste my money and none of my clothes be dried at all and as for my sheets, jacket and sweater I put in the big dryer to not feel like it got dried at all and when I came back the lady said it was to much clothes even though it was only a little bit of clothes one load to be exact now I'm spending more money to dry them again... SMH WHY HAVE WORKERS WHO DONT SPEAK ENGLISH OR UNDERSTAND WHAT THE ENGLISH CUSTOMERS ARE COMPLAINING ABOUT
